*Homomorphic Encryption, allows users to secure and leave their data in an encrypted format even while it is being processed or manipulated. Encryption and decryption are done by the same key holder. It enables a user to encrypt the confidential data and out source it to the enterprise via cloud services to process the given data

*Trusted Platform Module (TPM), is a crypto processor or chip that is present on the motherboard that can securely store the encryption keys, and it can perform many cryptographic operations

